# {{grammar}} A pronoun that does not [[specify]] the [[identity]] of its [[referent]]. In English, the suffixes -ever and -soever may be added to ''what'', ''which'', ''who'', and ''whom'' to obtain indefinite pronouns.
#*Example: "any" and "some" in "If there's any more, I want some."
#*Example: "whomever" in "Bring whomever you wish."

